29 "§ 135-154. North Carolina Teachers' and State Employees' Benefit Trust.
30 (a) Benefit Trust. – A trust fund, the North Carolina Teachers' and State Employees'
31 Benefit Trust, is hereby created as a master trust to which all receipts, transfers, appropriations,
32 contributions, investment earnings, and other income belonging to the Plans participating plans
33 shall be deposited, and from which all benefits and expenses against the Plans those participating
34 plans shall be disbursed. It is the intent of the General Assembly that a this master trust fund be
35 created that provides provide an irrevocable source of funding to be used, to the extent the fund's
36 assets are sufficient, only for death benefits and disability benefits payable to the Plans' members,
37 participants, and beneficiaries, pursuant to G.S. 120 4.27, G.S. 128 27(l), subsections (l2) through
38 (l6) of G.S. 128 27, 135 5(l), 135 64(k), and 143 166.60. beneficiaries of the participating plans
39 and reasonable expenses for the administration of the participating plans. The Boards of Trustees
40 of the Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System and the Local Governmental
41 Employees' Retirement System shall be the trustee of the Benefit Trust.
42 (b) No Comingling of Funds. – Within the Benefit Trust, the funds of each of the Plans
43 participating plans shall be accounted for separately and not commingled.
44 (c) Assets. – Assets of one participating plan cannot be used to pay for liabilities of
45 another participating plan within the Benefit Trust. The assets of the trust fund Benefit Trust shall
46 be used only for the exclusive benefit of persons who are or may be entitled to benefits under the
47 Plans. participating plans. In no event, including dissolution, will the shall any assets of the trust
48 fund Benefit Trust be distributed to any entity that is not a state, a political subdivision of a state,
49 or another entity the income of which is excludable from its gross income by application of
50 section 115(1) of the Internal Revenue Code. The assets of the Benefit Trust are not subject to
51 the claims of creditors of the employers and non employers any of the following:
